Company Summary

Learning Network is a growing, innovative, and customer-centric educational technology company. We seek creative and tenacious individuals to help us drive success through service.




Service is very important to us. At Learning Network, you will be among real people who care - about their customers and their colleagues. We prioritize service by making sure the details are done and done well - every time. We make promises and we keep those promises. We recognize that our customers and our employees don’t have to choose us. As such, service is embedded deep within our culture - and white-glove service is an expectation of every employee.




At Learning Network, you’ll be a part of something special. You’ll sleep better knowing you make a difference by bringing access to the most innovative education to thousands of students. You’ll do this amongst a supportive community of people who care. In return, you’ll care. You’ll show you care by being teachable; by not only doing your job well but by valuing the relationships with those you work with. You’ll achieve your goals and play nicely in the sandbox with others while doing it. We don’t do drama and neither should you.




Working at Learning Network isn’t for everyone. But for those who choose to commit to hard work, service, students, and colleagues, it’s an incredibly rewarding experience.




Position Summary

We have an immediate opening for a Marketing Analyst. In this role, you will collect and analyze data to identify the ideal audiences for Learning Network's services. You will assess campaign effectiveness, identify optimizations for marketing strategies, and make recommendations based on your findings.




To be successful, you’ll need to be a detail-oriented, initiative taker. We need a broad thinker who can make suggestions, take constructive feedback with a good attitude and without pushback, and then go out and personally execute with diligence. If you like conducting market research, gathering and analyzing data, and building marketing plans, we’re probably a good fit.




This position is full-time and based work from home.




Job Duties

 * Serve all stakeholders with integrity, humility, and joy while consistently modeling the importance of both task competency and relationships;
 * Participate in Company events, activities, and meetings with a smile and an infectious, great attitude;
 * Measure and report on key performance indicators (KPIs) and return on investment (ROI) for marketing campaigns throughout their entire lifecycle;
 * Integrate and analyze data from various marketing channels (e.g., email, social media, SEM, website) to provide a holistic view of marketing performance;
 * Provide actionable insights and recommendations with data visualizations on how to optimize various campaign performance;
 * Utilize tools like Tableau, Power BI, Dataiku, or similar to present data in an understandable format;
 * Identify opportunities for cross-channel marketing initiatives;
 * Use predictive modeling techniques to forecast future trends and marketing outcomes;
 * Conduct market research to compare SEM, campaigns, trends, opportunities, and competitor activities;
 * Support the development and movement of SEO keywords through comprehensive analytics and reporting;
 * Assist in tracking and analyzing marketing spending and outcomes;
 * Analyze landing page performance and lead A/B testing initiatives to improve conversion rates continuously;
 * Monitor and report on overall website traffic and user behavior to identify opportunities for optimization;
 * Assist in planning and measuring the success of marketing events, including collecting and analyzing data to evaluate their effectiveness and impact;
 * Ensure the accuracy and integrity of marketing data by maintaining clean and organized databases, including implementing best practices for data management and analytics;
 * All other duties as assigned.




Essential Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities

 * Strong interpersonal skills with the demonstrated ability to consistently lead and serve others with humility, kindness, empathy, and joy;
 * Strong analytical, critical thinking, and problem-solving skills with the ability to interpret complex data sets and draw actionable insights;
 * Excellent written and verbal communication skills with the ability to effectively present complex information and impactful data visualizations to stakeholders at all levels;
 * Strong active listening with the ability to lead, collaborate, and work effectively in team and cross-functional team environments;
 * Strong understanding of marketing principles, trends, and best practices;
 * Excellent organizational skills with the ability to maintain clean and organized databases;
 * Ability to juggle multiple tasks, changing priorities, and changing business needs in a fast-paced environment while managing and meeting deadlines;
 * Ability to establish rapport, gain commitment, and provide a high level of support to internal and external stakeholders;
 * Understanding of customer journeys and experience optimization;
 * Ability to conduct market research and competitor analysis; and
 * High level of accuracy and attention to detail in data analysis and reporting with a demonstrated commitment to achieving daily performance metrics and quality standards, and continuous pursuit of improvement and innovation in marketing analytics.




Qualifications

 * Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Business Administration, Statistics, or a related field required;
 * Minimum three (3) years of experience in a marketing analyst or similar role required;
 * Minimum three (3) years of experience with data analysis tools such as Excel, Google Analytics, and data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, Dataiku required;
 * Minimum two (2) years of experience with SQL and marketing automation platforms required;
 * Strong experience with Mac OS, Google Workspace, and Asana preferred;
 * Private, distraction-free, professional remote work environment with high-speed internet; and
 * Ability to pass required background checks.




Notice for Colorado Residents: In any materials you submit as part of Learning Network's application process, you may redact or remove age-identifying information such as age, date of birth, or dates of school attendance or graduation. You will not be penalized for redacting or removing this information.




Benefits

 * Medical, dental, and vision employee coverage for as little as $1 each per month;
 * Personal paid time off in addition to major holidays;
 * Short-term disability insurance, long-term disability insurance, life insurance, and AD&D insurance all 100% paid by the employer; and
 * 401(k) with employer contributing a dollar-for-dollar match of employee contributions up to 5% of employee earnings.

Introduction

Discover a world of endless possibilities at Gallagher Benefit Services, where you'll have the power to shape the future of workplaces across industries. As a member of our team, you become the driving force behind positive change, helping clients build environments where employees thrive. Embrace the opportunity to impact lives, unlock potential, and create a legacy of remarkable transformation.

We believe that every candidate brings something special to the table, including you! So, even if you feel that you’re close but not an exact match, we encourage you to apply.

Overview

This position will play a critical role in providing (ongoing or custom) reporting, analytics and data-driven insights that support the effective design and management of our clients’ benefit plans. This role will collaborate closely with Financial Benefit Consultants and Actuarial Consultants, fulfilling both custom and ad hoc requests from our approved data warehouse platforms. In addition, this role will play an important part in developing book of business insights that further Gallagher’s reputation as a thought leader in the benefits market. As a key member of the Insights & Analysis team, successful candidates must possess strong technical skills and be strong problem solvers and critical thinkers.

How You'll Make An Impact

Client & Prospect Support


 * Develop and deploy aligned divisional processes, templates and dashboards for bringing best-in-class data analytic solutions to drive improved decision making and business performance for our clients;
 * Support creation of ad hoc queries and deliver custom reporting / analyses and presentations using SQL, web-based query builders from approved data warehouses, Microsoft Excel or other analytic tools;
 * Work collaboratively with Financial & Actuarial Consulting and branch account team members to determine clients’ analytics needs and deliver meaningful and actionable reporting and analytics solutions;
 * Support key prospect targets with data-driven insights, as needed;
 * Work closely with Data & Insights Lead, as well as the Director, Insights & Analysis and other key stakeholders to develop, improve and build upon our toolbox of benefits-focused analytic deliverables across the division;
 * Support internal trainings of FAC teams – both divisional and regional – as well as supporting branch-level promotion of data & analytics services and capabilities.



Insights & Thought Leadership


 * Work with Data & Insights Lead to create and deploy a regular cadence of meaningful book of business insights and trends;
 * Support divisional marketing and thought leadership initiatives with data-driven Health & Benefits insights and trends from our combined databases in GBSInsider;
 * Collaborate with New Business Intelligence team to regularly update metrics in support of prospect opportunity analyses – including book of business data, as well as data cuts by industry, size and/or geography.



Technical Expertise


 * Work to develop and maintain expert-level knowledge of all GBS approved data warehouse platforms, learning coding languages and/or different dashboard capabilities, as needed;
 * Continue to build technical skills on core tools and platforms – both through informal trainings and self-guided learning;
 * Supporting large analytics projects from start to finish, as needed;
 * Work to develop strong data storytelling capabilities and use those skills to create and present compelling and actionable analytics;
 * Identify ongoing process improvement opportunities, and assist in the design, testing, documentation and implementation of process enhancements – also identifying opportunities for automation as they arise.



Competencies, Expertise and Business Acumen


 * Excellent verbal and written communication;
 * Strong strategic thinker and incredibly collaborative – both with internal team members and other divisional stakeholders;
 * Shows interest and potential to be an excellent “data storyteller”;
 * Self-starter with superb research skills and a general mindset of curiosity – investigating key drivers and root causes in data;
 * Creative problem solver with strong critical thinking and analytical skills – collecting, organizing, analyzing and presenting significant amounts of information with attention to detail;
 * Feels comfortable in giving and receiving constructive feedback;
 * Strong interpersonal skills and ability to develop and maintain professional relationships with internal and external stakeholders;
 * Consistently meets deadlines, and works well collaboratively as well as independently;
 * Ability to sell the value of GBS data analytics products and services by illustrating potential impact to prospects and clients.



Customer Service and Business Strategy


 * Builds knowledge of Gallagher tools, systems and shared resources;
 * Consistently follows client service workflows to ensure efficiency, timeliness and accuracy of execution;
 * Is willing to go the “Extra Mile” to achieve results that benefit the client, the Branch and Gallagher;
 * Accountable for meeting timeline of key analytics deliverables with consistency and accuracy;
 * Is able to adapt quickly to a variety of circumstances, and change approach when necessary.



About You


 * Bachelor’s Degree in STEM or Business-related field, and 3+ years of health plan financial, data mining or reporting experience;
 * Data Science, Analytics, Mathematics or Statistics background preferred, but not required;
 * Advanced Excel and data analysis skills, including a working knowledge of PowerBI and/or SQL;
 * A quick study with interest in learning new skills, tools and data platforms.



Compensation And Benefits

On top of a competitive salary, great teams and exciting career opportunities, we also offer a wide range of benefits.

Below are the minimum core benefits you’ll get, depending on your job level these benefits may improve:


 * Medical/dental/vision plans, which start from day one!
 * Life and accident insurance
 * 401(K) and Roth options
 * Tax-advantaged accounts (HSA, FSA)
 * Educational expense reimbursement
 * Paid parental leave



Other benefits include:


 * Digital mental health services (Talkspace)
 * Flexible work hours (availability varies by office and job function)
 * Training programs
 * Gallagher Thrive program – elevating your health through challenges, workshops and digital fitness programs for your overall wellbeing
 * Charitable matching gift program
 * And more...



